LONDON: Fans desperate for a sneak peek of the Jeddah Corniche circuit were given a treat on Monday after Codemasters and Electronic Arts — creators of the F1 2021 video game — released a video of the track to be included in the game. The first ever Saudi Arabian Grand Prix is now less than three weeks away, with drivers such as Lewis Hamilton and Max Verstappen set to race around what will be the longest — and fastest — street circuit on the Formula 1 calendar on Dec. 3-5. Take a rapid lap of the new Jeddah Corniche Circuit The fastest street circuit on the calendar is now available on the #F12021Game #F1 @Formula1game — Formula 1 (@F1) November 15, 2021 “The circuit in Jeddah will be extraordinary,” F1 track designer Carsten Tilke told F1.com. “It will be a different kind of street track, something the world has never seen before.” The Jeddah Corniche circuit consists of 27 turns and extends for a length of 6.175 kilometers, making it the longest street circuit, and the second longest circuit in the current Formula 1 season's calendar behind the prestigious Belgian circuit Spa-Francorchamps.